Context: From Edward Thomas, "I Never Saw That Land Before" and from Tu Fu, "Conscripts Leaving for the Frontier." Trans. Charles Budd
Question: Choose the poem that uses onomatopoeia.
Options: (A) To the valley and the river small,
The cattle, the grass, the bare ash trees,
The chickens from the farmsteads, all
Elm-hidden, and the tributaries (B) Chariots rumbling; horses neighing;
Soldiers shouting martial cries;
Drums are sounding; trumpets braying;
Seas of glittering spears arise.

