Question: Adapted from J. R. Dos Passos, "The Bridge" and from Walt Whitman, "Salut au Monde!"
Options: (A) The lonely bridge cuts dark across the marsh
Whose long pools glow with the light
Of a flaming summer sunset.
At this end limp bushes overhang,
Palely reflected in the amber-colored water. (B) I see the tracks of the railroads of the earth;
I see them welding State to State, city to city, through North America;
I see them in Great Britain, I see them in Europe;
I see them in Asia and in Africa.
